---
interface Props {
  class?: string;
}

const { class: className = '' } = Astro.props;
---

<section id="problem" class={`section py-24 relative ${className}`}>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold mb-6">
        The CLI
        <span class="block bg-gradient-to-r from-red-600 to-orange-600 dark:from-red-400 dark:to-orange-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
          Barrier
        </span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        ClaudeKit is incredibly powerful for everyone â€” but the CLI interface creates unnecessary friction for non-tech users
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="feature-card glass-card rounded-2xl p-8 border border-red-500/20 hover:border-red-500/40 cursor-pointer">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-red-500/20 to-orange-500/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-red-500 dark:text-red-400" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><polyline points="8 7 12 12 8 17"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-red-500 dark:text-red-400">Terminal Interface</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">60+ slash commands to memorize. Terminal commands feel intimidating if you're not a developer.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card glass-card rounded-2xl p-8 border border-orange-500/20 hover:border-orange-500/40 cursor-pointer">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/20 to-amber-500/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-500 dark:text-orange-400" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-orange-500 dark:text-orange-400">Learning Curve</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Which workflow? Which command sequence? How do I combine them? Takes time to master the CLI patterns.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card glass-card rounded-2xl p-8 border border-amber-500/20 hover:border-amber-500/40 cursor-pointer">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500/20 to-yellow-500/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400">No Safety Net</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">One wrong command can lose progress. No undo button. No visual feedback on what's happening.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>